Response: There is no limit to the number of nodes you can create at each level. You can add nodes as needed.

Question: Here, you mean at each level. Is there an upper limit on the total levels of nodes?
Response: Yes, you are right! So far, our context tree only supports 3 levels. When designing the context tree, be careful to the level restriction.

Question: Hi, I cannot add a child node to the 4th level of the context tree. How can I fix this?
Response: Oh, sorry to inform you that our context tree only supports up to 3 levels of design. I am afraid you have to get rid of the 4th level or simplify your design to 3 levels.

Question: Ok, got it! I will modify it.
Response: You can modify it offline and then upload the modified file, or modify online in the workspace and save the updated version.

Question: What’s the recommended number of input features for a context tree? Is there any limit?
Response: There is no limit to the number of nodes and child nodes, but tree should have only three levels.

Question: Got it! Will too many nodes affect efficiency?
Response: Great question! The greater the number of nodes, the more test cases will be generated and the longer it will take. So if possible create a tree with necessary key values.

Question: How can I organize the context features? Can you provide a template?
Response: You can organize your context features into a tree structure level by level. A parent node presents a context feature, and a child node presents a subfeature of that context feature.

Question: How many subfeatures can I add to a context feature?
Response: There is no limit to the number of subfeatures you can add. But be careful, our context tree design only supports up to 3 levels.

Question: How can I change the order between features?
Response: Go to  Login → Get Started → DATA ADMINISTRATION WITH GRAPH

Question: I tried to rearrange the order of child nodes in my tree but failed. Can you help me figure it out?
Response: I am sorry. Users are not allowed to do that directly. Nodes and child Nodes are sorted based on name (A-Z) after each action (add, delete and rename).

Question: What actions can I do to a node in the context tree?
Response: You can add, delete or rename a node in the context tree.

Question: How can I delete or add a node?
Response: Navigation : Login → Get Started → DATA ADMINISTRATION WITH GRAPH. Hover mouse on the target node, and right click. You'll see the corresponding options.

Question: Does the order of nodes at each level matter?
Response: The order of nodes at each level will be automatically sorted based on name (A-Z) after each action. The order doesn't affect test cases generation.

Question: If I add more than 10 nodes at a level, would it be too much?
Response: Actually, there is no restrictions. However, more nodes will take more time to generate test cases and modeling inputs.

Question: I mistakenly deleted the context tree I just created. Is there any way to restore it?
Response: Did you save it? You can only restore info from the saved tree.

Question: I didn't. Do I need to rebuild it from scratch?
Response: I am sorry, the answer is YES.

Question: The webpage was frozen when I was creating the context tree. If I refresh this page, will I lose my records?
Response: Did you save it? You can only restore records from the saved tree. If you didn't, you'll lose all the info.

Question: I saved! Where can I find the saved version.
Response: Go to  Login → Get Started → DATA ADMINISTRATION WITH GRAPH. Select tree/file from dropdown list.

Question: How can I correct the typo in my node label?
Response: Move the mouse over the node. Right click on it and select “Rename Node” option. A popup window will open.Change name and Click rename.

Question: Oh, thanks. Clear instructions.
Response: No problem. Just let you know, when you rename a node, the order of nodes will be automatically sorted by new name (A-Z).

Question: How can I zoom in the tree I built, because all the nodes are squeezed together?
Response: There are three ways. 1. Click near the tree Area (If tree is not manipulated). Use mouse scroll to zoom-in and zoom-out the tree.

Question: 2. Click and hold to move tree around.
Response: 3. Double click near the tree to zoom-in.

Question: Can I specify the file save path in advance instead of selecting it every time?
Response: No, we don't have that option. We utilize systems file explorer. But once user opens the directory and selects a file, the same directory will open during the user session.

Question: If I switch to other app and come back, the same directory still open?
Response: Not exactly. The same directory stays open only if you only use this app.

Question: I’d like to turn a sub-feature into a higher level feature, and how can I make this modification?
Response: Go to  Login → Get Started → DATA ADMINISTRATION WITH GRAPH. Drag and rearrange nodes feature is available. You can modify the tree this way.

Question: Can I perform the same operation to downgrade a feature to a lower level?
Response: Exactly. The operation is the same.

Question: Can I add multiple nodes to my context tree at once?
Response: Of course. Mouse hover on a node and right click. Choose the "Create Child Node" option. You can customize the nodes to be added in the popup window.

Question: Could you explain in more detail?
Response: Sure.There is a plus(+) symbol on the popup window. With this you can add as many nodes required, then click create to add nodes to the tree.

Question: Can I merge the nodes at level 2 and level 3 in my context tree?
Response: Do you mean reconstruct your context tree? Of course, you can do it.

Question: How can I achieve it?
Response: Go to  Login → Get Started → DATA ADMINISTRATION WITH GRAPH. Drag and rearrange nodes feature is available .

Question: Hi, where can I find my saved context tree file?
Response: Select tree/file from dropdown list. Tree will be displayed.

Question: Can I continue to modify on it?
Response: Sure. But don't forget to save your changes.

Question: Can I build two separate context trees in the file?
Response: Could you elaborate a bit more on "separate context trees" you mentioned ?

Question: What I mean is to create two separate trees with separate roots.
Response: At this stage, our application does not support multiple context trees in a file. A file only contains a tree.

Question: Can I create my context tree offline and then upload the file?
Response: Sure. You can choose to upload files or create online.

Question: What format does the app support?
Response: JSON. You should build your context tree as a json file.

Question: Can I download the context tree I built on the app?
Response: Yes. After you save it, we can download the corresponding json file generated by the app.

Question: Great! If I want to modify the tree, I need to upload the file again?
Response: Yes, that's one way. Another way is to modify the json file directly.

Question: What actions can I do to a tree node?
Response: Actions, such as add, delete, rename and etc. You can find different actions in the option list.

Question: Where can I find the option list you mentioned?
Response: Mouse hovers on a node and right click, then the option list will appear.

Question: Can I merge the child nodes of a node to another node at the same level?
Response: Yes, you can. Just drag and rearrange the nodes in your tree.

Question: Great! What's the upper bound of the number of child nodes?
Response: There is no limit. You can add child nodes as needed.

Question: I have been waiting for the test cases to be generated for a long time. It takes like forever...
Response: May I ask how many nodes in your context tree?

Question: Over 100 nodes.
Response: The more nodes, the more test cases will be generated. It will take a looooong time. So if possible delete some redundant nodes and just retain the key ones.

Question: It took me a long time to generate all the test cases. Is there a problem with too many nodes in my context tree?
Response: I think you created too many nodes in you context tree. You can delete some redundant nodes and just keep the important ones.

Question: How can I delete a node?
Response: Mouse hovers on a node and right click. Then you will see the delete option.

Question: While building the context tree, my web page was frozen. what should I do?
Response: Probably you could try to refresh the page and redraw your tree.

Question: You mean if I refresh I will lose what I have built so far!?
Response: Sorry, if the network connection is lost, we will not be able to recover what you created. Try to save the file often.

Question: There is little room for me to add nodes to the third level of the context tree.
Response: Do you want to zoom in or zoom out the tree?

Question: Yes, I would like to zoom out a bit. How can I do that?
Response: Mouse scroll to zoom-in and zoom-out the tree, or click and hold to move tree around.

Question: How many contents can I add to my context?
Response: Do you mean how many nodes you can add to your context tree? Am I right?

Question: Yes, that's exactly what I mean. I want to know the limit to the number of nodes I can add to the tree.
Response: There is no limit to the number of nodes in the context tree, but you can only have one root.

Question: Can I merge two context trees into a single one online?
Response: I am afraid you can't do it online. Because in the online editing, we only allow to add one and only one root node.

Question: Is there any other way to merge two context trees? I don't want to build the merged tree from scratch.
Response: You can merge the two tree files offline. And then upload the merged JSON file.

Question: What's the maximum depth of the context tree?
Response: The context tree should have up to 3 levels.

Question: Can we specify the weights on the edge of the tree?
Response: Sorry, now we don't have this function.

Question: Can we customize property to each node?
Response: What do you mean by property?

Question: I mean the node detail, such as creation time, last modification time, number of children and etc.
Response: Sorry, now we only support adding category names to each node.

Question: How many parents can each child node have?
Response: In our application, each child node can have and only have one parent node.

Question: Got it. And how many child nodes can each node have?
Response: There is no limit to the number of child nodes.

Question: Can we have customized shape of nodes when drawing the tree?
Response: Sorry, we don't have such function.

Question: Maybe you should add this functionality in the futher. I think it's important for users to classify nodes in different groups.
Response: Thanks for your suggestion. We'll think about it.
